Pre-Game Insights: Gambia have arguably turned out their best-ever side in recent times and came into this competition with loads of confidence, having recently qualified for a third consecutive Africa Cup of Nations.
Ivory Coast have been unable to qualify for the last two editions of the FIFA World Cup, having previously made three consecutive appearances in 2006, 2010 and 2014.
The Elephants were simply too strong in their demolition of Seychelles in their opening match of qualifying, with Karim Konate and Hamed Traore scoring two goals each.
The visitors are ranked 52nd in the world according to the latest FIFA World Rankings.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Gambia have featured in the continent’s biggest tournament only two years ago.
This match marks Ivory Coast’s first encounter against Gambia in a decade, with their last meeting occurring in June 2013.
